  "description": [
    "PAGE FOUR town crier IPLEDGED TO COMMUNITY SERVICE sA 6669500 6669570 Published weekly on Wednesday at 75 Market Square Newington PHILIP CALDERAZZI Publisher GORDON E HALL Managing Editor NATALIE ROME Associate Editor PEGGY COCHEO Account Executive CECILIA HALL Staff Artist 175 six months 300 year Second Class Postage Paid at Hartford Connecticut Editorials Survival Security Everyone today is looking for security The adult for security in his job children for security from their parents in the form of love and discipline and our gov ernment along with most sanethinking world govern ments the security of World Peace But life is not made up of security but of unex pected and sometimes unhappy events However we work and plan to the best of our ability for security for our loved ones We pay for life and hospital insurance ire insurance on our property contribute to Social Security so that we may have a pension in our later years guide love and educate our children so that they have security in their lives butwhat about security of our very life The security of surviving in case of war Have we planned or even taken the trouble to learn the facts about our"
